9\. Framework Governance

9.1 Integration with Existing Processes

This Layer 4 process integrates with the following existing artifacts:

-   **BACKLOG.md:** The project backlog (BACKLOG.md) is the current
    operational implementation of this process during POC development.
    At production deployment, defects are managed in the unified defect
    record system described in Layer 3, Section 6. During POC, the
    priority definitions (P0--P4) and category tags from BACKLOG.md
    align with this framework.

-   **BUILD_HISTORY.md:** Every defect resolution during POC is
    documented in BUILD_HISTORY.md as a decision record, providing the
    audit trail required by this framework.

-   **SYNC_LOG.md:** Defects that originate from discrepancies between
    the analysis environment and the build environment are tracked
    through SYNC_LOG.md, then formalized as defect records once
    classified.

9.2 Document Series

1.  **Prevention & Design Review Framework (Layer 1)** --- completed

2.  **Verification & Test Execution Framework (Layer 2)** --- completed

3.  **Defect Monitoring Dashboard Specification (Layer 3)** ---
    completed

4.  **Defect Resolution & Prioritized Backlog Process (Layer 4)** ---
    this document

5.  **Unified Defect Taxonomy & Metrics (Layer 5)** --- consolidation
    document

9.3 Continuous Improvement

The resolution process itself is subject to improvement. Quarterly
retrospectives review resolution metrics and identify process
bottlenecks. Common improvement areas include: SLA recalibration based
on observed capacity, checklist refinement when new defect patterns
emerge, and automation of routine verification steps as the system
matures through trust phases (ADR-001).

> *The five-layer defect management system is designed as a closed loop.
> Prevention (Layer 1) reduces defects. Testing (Layer 2) catches what
> prevention misses. The dashboard (Layer 3) makes defects visible.
> Resolution (Layer 4) eliminates them. Each defect resolved feeds back
> into prevention---the root cause analysis informs design review
> improvements, the regression test prevents recurrence, and the metrics
> reveal systemic patterns that drive process change.*
